## Context

RDJ-26561 R&R (tracker 0274), remarks ED-01 (dedup part), R1-12. The referee:
DOI-based dedup misses WP-vs-published pairs (different or absent DOIs);
title+year dedup misses them too (dates and sometimes titles differ). Suggests
incorporating the author variable. Asks for the number of duplicates removed
by each procedure: (1) DOI-based, (2) title+year matching.

The counts themselves are produced by ticket 0284 (pipeline artifact, possibly
padme-side); this ticket is the manuscript revision that cites them.

## Relevant files

- `deliverables/data-paper/data-paper.qmd` — Method section, dedup paragraph
- 0284's counts artifact (path recorded in that ticket on close)

## Actions

1. Add the per-procedure counts (from 0284's artifact) and an honest
   discussion of WP-vs-published residual duplicates to the paper.
2. Evaluate (possibly as future work rather than implementation) author-aware
   dedup; state the decision and its rationale in the text or response letter.

